The paper deals with video content analysis, specifically action localization in long untrimmed videos. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves deep learning techniques, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The framework also involves refinement and regression techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on a benchmark dataset, which suggests the involvement of information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
